title: Grateful Dead Live at Hofheinz Pavilion on 1972-11-19
description:
Set 1

Bertha, Me & My Uncle, Sugaree, Beat It On Down The Line, Bird Song, Black Throated Wind, Don't Ease Me In, Mexicali Blues, Box Of Rain, Tomorrow Is Forever, Big River, China Cat Sunflower-> I Know You Rider, Playin' In The Band, Casey Jones

Set 2

Promised Land, Ramble On Rose, El Paso, Stella Blue, Jack Straw, Dark Star-> Weather Report Suite Prelude-> Mississippi Half Step, Around & Around, Big Railroad Blues, Sugar Magnolia-> Goin' Down The Road Feelin' Bad

'Stars & Stripes Forever' tuning before 'Tomorrow Is Forever' 'Nickelodeon' tuning be ore 'Playin' 'Dixie' tuning before 'Dark Star"

reviews.review_text: Excellent recording, awesome Darkstar Love the Darkstar on this, probably the best of the bunch where Phil took a long solo.  Lots of other great jamming and crystal clear sound.
highlights abound Box>Playin' each version is super hot.

great show stumbled upon this when looking at shows somewhat close to dave's picks 11 (wichita 11/17/72)... easy five star w/ gorgeous sound post-bertha opener.

btwind, box, playin, dark star, wrs, stella blue, several others top rate...
Phil's Rockin' Great bass throughout. Sounds like they cranked Phil up I'm this one.
Excellent Forecast With the ever-present chance of lingering Dark Star spaciness, this Weather Report Suite is well worth a good listen. The mix is a Phil fan's fantasy.

Me & My Uncle Lyric Change Did anyone else notice that Bob sings "I grabbed a bottle, cracked him in the jaw" instead of the usual "I shot him down, Lord, he never saw."  Does anyone know of other times he changed this lyric?  Also, if you haven't read the origin story for this song, it is a good one- check it out in the Annotated Lyrics.
Bird song! Yet another amazing version from Nov 72
